            <h1> Crazy Stupid Love</h1>
            <h2>Director: Glenn Ficarra, John Requa</h2>
            <h3>Genre: Romance/Drama</h3>
            <h4>Year Released: 2011</h4>
            <h5>Awards:People's Choice Award: Best Actress, female</h5>
            <h6>Fun Fact: The Dirty Dancing lift scene had to be altered because of Stone's unexpected fear of heights</h6>
            </div>
            <!-- This section contains the introduction paragraph -->
            <p id="intro">
                When Cal Weaver’s wife Emily asks for a divorce after admitting she cheated, his perfect suburban life falls apart. <br> He starts frequenting bars, where smooth-talking ladies’ man Jacob Palmer takes him under his wing and teaches him how to flirt and date again. <br>
                Meanwhile, Jacob unexpectedly falls for Hannah, a woman who challenges his player lifestyle. <br>
                As relationships and identities intertwine, including Cal’s son having a crush on his babysitter. Everything comes to a chaotic and funny climax when the truth comes out.

In the end, love proves messy, unpredictable, but <strong> worth it. </strong> 
</p>
